<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870831-0031 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Blount Inc.</HL><DD> 08/31/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BLTA </IN><TEXT>   Blount Inc., Montgomery, Ala., said it will take a $4.3 million charge in the fiscal second quarter ending today for costs associated with settling a lawsuit, the closing of three offices and increased insurance reserves.    Blount, a construction, engineering and specialty steel concern, had year-earlier earnings of $2.7 million, or 23 cents a share, on revenue of $358.6 million.    Blount said the lawsuit settlement, involving its Blount Brothers Corp. construction unit, will result in a charge of $3.1 million, or 26 cents a share. An additional charge of $1.2 million, or 10 cents a share, will result from expenses associated with the previously announced closing of three regional construction offices and from the increased insurance reserves. </TEXT></DOC>